##	user guide/build requirements

 
The functions in main.py are used to download data from yahoo finance using mongodb. The russell2000 index is omitted for runtime considerations.


The function "regression" in reg.py regresses the chosen index onto up to 10 assets, over a given time window. 
The results (fitted vs. actual) are displayed as a scatterplot, and the summary of the regression object is displayed.
The function "subset" identifies a subset of assets which correlate most with the first principal component. This can be used to identify which assets to use in the regression.


The function "get_most_correlated_pairs" in pairs.py identifies the pairs of assets with the greatest absolute correlation, and calculates the mean reversion speed for their spreads.
The function "trade" executes a pairs trading strategy for two given stocks, depending on starting capital, a lookback period, and entry and exit thresholds. 
The history of positions, portfolio value, and returns are given, as well as the sharpe and sortino ratios.


"dashboard.py" contains an executable dashboard for the pairs strategy. This has input options for the strategy parameters, and outputs a graph and table of summaries.



